(271, 5, 'gTQpZW', 2826, 'Fruites and VegitablesFresh FruitsGreen houseOrange - ImportedOrange - ImportedNA4PCS', 'Vegitable and Fruits ', 'Fruites and Vegitables', 'Fresh Fruits', 'Green house', 'Orange - Imported', 'Orange - Imported', 'NA', 'Fresho brings you an assortment of 4 imported oranges, which make for an ideal gift during the festive season or even for making desserts and juices. These imported oranges are much bigger in size as compared to the Indian counterpart. You will notice their skin is much brighter and vibrant too. Easy to peel, these oranges are a healthy snack alternative.', 4, 'PCS', 4, 138, 110, 'https://www.bigbasket.com/media/uploads/p/l/20000909_18-fresho-orange-imported.jpg', 0, '', '2022-01-06 00:00:00', '2022-01-06 00:00:00', 1, 0),
(272, 5, 'gTQpZW', 2827, 'Fruites and VegitablesFresh FruitsGreen houseOrange - ImportedOrange - ImportedNA6PCS', 'Vegitable and Fruits ', 'Fruites and Vegitables', 'Fresh Fruits', 'Green house', 'Orange - Imported', 'Orange - Imported', 'NA', 'Navel oranges are very sugary and juicy and considered to be the world\'s finest orange for fresh consumption because they are very sweet, naturally juice, seedless and peels and segments very easily. It has a variety of phytochemicals containing flavanoids hesperetin, beta-carotene and carotenoids alpha etc. It is wealthy in Vitamin C, A and Folate and includes small amounts of Vitamin E & B complex vitamins too.\r\n Product image shown is for representation purpose only, the actually product may vary based on season, produce & availability.', 6, 'PCS', 6, 203, 162, 'https://www.bigbasket.com/media/uploads/p/l/20000910_12-fresho-orange-imported.jpg', 0, '', '2022-01-06 00:00:00', '2022-01-06 00:00:00', 1, 0),
(273, 5, 'gTQpZW', 2828, 'Fruites and VegitablesFresh FruitsGreen housePapayaPapaya SmallNA1PCS', 'Vegitable and Fruits ', 'Fruites and Vegitables', 'Fresh Fruits', 'Green house', 'Papaya', 'Papaya Small', 'NA', 'Papayas grow in tropical climates and are also known as papaws or pawpaws. Initially green and somewhat bitter in taste, papayas are butter-yellow when fully ripe and shaped like a pear.\r\n Their pale-orange flesh has dozens of small, black, sticky seeds at the center, similar to a melon.', 1, 'PCS', 1, 38, 30, 'https://www.bigbasket.com/media/uploads/p/l/40114961_3-fresho-papaya-small.jpg', 0, '', '2022-01-06 00:00:00', '2022-01-06 00:00:00', 1, 0),
